cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sentiment classification over constituent trees using neural models. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves deep learning techniques for sentiment representation. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves modeling sentiment composition. It may also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves neural models and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it uses ELMo embeddings for sentiment classification.
